race.comment: SWEET JUSTICE (13) has been racing well in tougher class and looks ideally placed coming back a notch. Worth noting two runs this time in have been on top of the ground but best form including sole win have been in rain-affected going. Gets chance to find some winning form. CHILLI REAPER (12) ran on hard fresh and narrowly missed. Fitter and drawn for a good run. Just missed the only other try second-up and expected to be in the finish again. WINNING WITNESS (16) was well below best last time. Looks nicely placed with the claim and drawn for a soft run. Can atone.  KING INCANTO (7) is mixing form but will appreciate the softer ground underfoot and gets chance to find best.
race.rail_position: +4m from the 400m to the winning post, True Remainder. (Pent: 5.60)
